y.newInstance\\\" could impact SecuritySupport12 rather than the base, so I’ll have to check that. Additionally, I need to distinguish the class loader resource call site in the active base. Should I verify if newSecuritySupport() returns a SecuritySupport12 object from its static initializer? Since we instantiate the constructor of the base class directly, Class.forName will initialize the class statically, yet the constructor is from the base. I see that the method dispatch goes to the base as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing class and resource handling**\\n\\nI need to make sure I'm not using getInstance since that would return a subclass. That’s good to keep in mind. I should also find a Jar helper resource, and maybe I can adapt and generalize in a new file. I suspect the package shouldn't be classified as a library, but \\\"xerces.xmlParserAPIs\\\" is acceptable. I think I don’t need to run the tests, but maybe I should compile to inspect the style.\\n\\nThere’s a potential concern regarding the class name \\\"TransformSecuritySupportTest,\\\" which doesn't map exactly. It's important to remember that dynamic access class classes should have their own files; this one is dedicated. However, since the active javax.xml.transform.SecuritySupport isn’t specified for package collisions, I’m considering a clearer name like \\\"JavaxXmlTransformSecuritySupportTest\\\" for better clarity.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_zuZRgjqR6LUGfuInzGgImBEv|fc_05a18ac5e7716b8d0169f8d40b535881a1b0d9694c816d04de", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/src/test/java/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/JavaxXmlTransformSecuritySupportTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage xerces.xmlParserAPIs;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNull;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.net.JarURLConnection;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\n\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class JavaxXmlTransformSecuritySupportTest {\n    private static final String SECURITY_SUPPORT_CLASS = \"javax.xml.transform.SecuritySupport\";\n    private static final String RESOURCE_NAME = \"xerces/xmlParserAPIs/transform-security-support-resource.txt\";\n    private static final String MISSING_RESOURCE_NAME = \"xerces/xmlParserAPIs/missing-transform-security-support-resource.txt\";\n\n    @Test\n    void getResourceAsStreamUsesProvidedClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        try (SecuritySupportInstance instance = newSecuritySupport()) {\n            Object securitySupport = instance.securitySupport();\n            Method getResourceAsStream = getResourceAsStreamMethod(securitySupport);\n            ResourceClassLoader classLoader = new ResourceClassLoader();\n\n            try (InputStream resource = (InputStream) getResourceAsStream.invoke(\n                    securitySupport,\n                    classLoader,\n                    RESOURCE_NAME)) {\n                assertNotNull(resource);\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void getResourceAsStreamUsesSystemClassLoaderWhenClassLoaderIsNull() throws Exception {\n        try (SecuritySupportInstance instance = newSecuritySupport()) {\n            Object securitySupport = instance.securitySupport();\n            Method getResourceAsStream = getResourceAsStreamMethod(securitySupport);\n\n            try (InputStream resource = (InputStream) getResourceAsStream.invoke(\n                    securitySupport,\n                    null,\n                    MISSING_RESOURCE_NAME)) {\n                assertNull(resource);\n            }\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static SecuritySupportInstance newSecuritySupport() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            return new SecuritySupportInstance(newSecuritySupport(Class.forName(SECURITY_SUPPORT_CLASS)), null);\n        } catch (ClassNotFoundException classNotFoundException) {\n            return newSecuritySupportFromLibraryJar(classNotFoundException);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Object newSecuritySupport(Class<?> securitySupportClass) throws Exception {\n        Constructor<?> constructor = securitySupportClass.getDeclaredConstructor();\n        constructor.setAccessible(true);\n        return constructor.newInstance();\n    }\n\n    private static SecuritySupportInstance newSecuritySupportFromLibraryJar(\n            ClassNotFoundException originalException) throws Exception {\n        File libraryJar = findXmlParserApisJar(originalException);\n        URLClassLoader classLoader = new URLClassLoader(new URL[] {libraryJar.toURI().toURL()}, null);\n        Class<?> securitySupportClass = Class.forName(SECURITY_SUPPORT_CLASS, true, classLoader);\n        return new SecuritySupportInstance(newSecuritySupport(securitySupportClass), classLoader);\n    }\n\n    private static File findXmlParserApisJar(ClassNotFoundException originalException) throws Exception {\n        String classPath = System.getProperty(\"java.class.path\", \"\");\n        for (String entry : classPath.split(File.pathSeparator)) {\n            File file = new File(entry);\n            if (isXmlParserApisJar(file)) {\n                return file;\n            }\n        }\n\n        ClassLoader classLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        Enumeration<URL> resources = classLoader.getResources(\"javax/xml/transform/SecuritySupport.class\");\n        while (resources.hasMoreElements()) {\n            URL resource = resources.nextElement();\n            if (\"jar\".equals(resource.getProtocol())) {\n                JarURLConnection connection = (JarURLConnection) resource.openConnection();\n                File file = new File(connection.getJarFileURL().toURI());\n                if (isXmlParserApisJar(file)) {\n                    return file;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        throw originalException;\n    }\n\n    private static boolean isXmlParserApisJar(File file) {\n        return file.getName().startsWith(\"xmlParserAPIs-\") && file.getName().endsWith(\".jar\");\n    }\n\n    private static Method getResourceAsStreamMethod(Object securitySupport) throws Exception {\n        Method method = securitySupport.getClass().getDeclaredMethod(\n                \"getResourceAsStream\",\n                ClassLoader.class,\n                String.class);\n        method.setAccessible(true);\n        return method;\n    }\n\n    private static final class SecuritySupportInstance implements AutoCloseable {\n        private final Object securitySupport;\n        private final URLClassLoader classLoader;\n\n        private SecuritySupportInstance(Object securitySupport, URLClassLoader classLoader) {\n            this.securitySupport = securitySupport;\n            this.classLoader = classLoader;\n        }\n\n        private Object securitySupport() {\n            return securitySupport;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void close() throws Exception {\n            if (classLoader != null) {\n                classLoader.close();\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ResourceClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n     